      "title": "Back Bonding",
      "conceptBody": "<h3><strong>Back Bonding</strong></h3><p>Sometimes, in order to make up electron deficiency in the central atom, the surrounding atom forms a $\\pi $-bond which is one side, i.e. shared electrons are contributed by surrounding atom only which is having lone pair of electrons. Over lap involves vacant orbital on the central atom and filled orbital on surrounding atom.</p><p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p>",
